title: Plane carrying 5 passengers crashes into Melbourne, Australia, mall - World - CBC News
text:
Plane carrying 5 passengers crashes into Melbourne, Australia, mall The plane crashed 45 minutes before the mall was supposed to open The Associated Press Posted: Feb 20, 2017 7:57 PM ET Last Updated: Feb 20, 2017 7:57 PM ET A light plane crashed into a shopping mall outside Melbourne, Australia. There was no immediate word about casualties. (Joe Castro/AAP/Associated Press) 
A light plane carrying five people crashed into a shopping mall on Tuesday in the city of Melbourne, Australia, officials said. 
There were no immediate reports of casualties, but the twin-engine Beechcraft Super King Air crashed about 45 minutes before the Direct Factory Outlet mall was to open, Police Minister Lisa Neville said. 
The plane had taken off from Melbourne's second-biggest airport at Essendon on a chartered flight to King Island, 255 kilometres to the south, Neville said. 
The mall adjoins the airport. 
Police Superintendent Mick Frewen said a pilot reported a "catastrophic engine failure" moments before the plane crashed into a storage area at the rear of the mall. 
Police and paramedics rushed to the crash site, where firefighters doused the flames. This video image shows the site of a plane crash near Essendon Airport in Melbourne, Australia Tuesday. (Channel 9/Associated Press)
